Key Match Events: Victor Wembanyama had 11 points in the third quarter to turn the tables on the Minnesota Timberwolves.
Wembanyama added 14 more points in the fourth quarter but missed a potential game-tying free throw with 18.0 seconds remaining.
Donte DiVincenzo missed a potential game-winning 3-pointer for the San Antonio Spurs.
Post-Match Reflections: Julius Randle would not give Wemby an inch, forcing Wembanyama to give up the ball late.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Spurs went to Wembanyama for the final shot but the Timberwolves defense held up.
